Neal specializes in narrative nonfiction, biography, and overlooked Americana. His fourth book, A CURIOUS MAN, chronicles the hard-to-believe life of the eccentric world-traveling cartoonist, media pioneer, millionaire-celebrity-playboy Robert 'Believe It or Not' Ripley, considered to be the godfather of reality TV. 
David Shields says A Curious Man &quot;constructs an elegant argument: the world Ripley created is the world in which we now live&quot;, and Ben Fountain says &quot;anyone who wants to understand America needs to read this book.&quot;
